This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to optimize reasoning in large knowledge bases. The focus is on commonsense knowledge, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of decision trees, which is a common machine learning technique, and therefore cs.LG is also likely. The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which fall under cs.CL. The paper also discusses the use of search algorithms, which is a key area of research in databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE).
